===  Noun ===
'''castle''' (plural '''[[castles]]''')

#A large building that is [[fortified]] and contains many [[defense]]s; in previous ages often inhabited by a [[nobleman]] or [[king]].
#A [[chess]] piece shaped like a castle [[tower]] which is also called a [[rook]].
#A [[close helmet]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1786''':  The castle was perhaps a figurative name for a close headpiece deduced from it's enclosing and defending the head, as a castle did the whole body; or a corruption from the Old French word Casquetel, a small or light helmet. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 12.

